General.Name: Kim Loong Resources Bhd
General.Description: Kim Loong Resources Berhad, an investment holding company, cultivates oil palm in Malaysia. The company operates in two segments, Plantation and Milling. It processes and markets oil palm and palm kernel products. The company also extracts residual oil from wet palm fiber; converts palm fiber; and manufactures health supplements and food ingredients. In addition, it engages in the trading of fresh fruit bunches; and biogas and power generation activities. As of January 31, 2022, it had a total plantation land holdings area of 16,922 hectares. The company was incorporated in 1975 and is based in Johor Bahru, Malaysia. Kim Loong Resources Berhad is a subsidiary of Sharikat Kim Loong Sendirian Berhad.
